        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 19 at 10:51AM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 1050 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Crystal Lake, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oakwood Hills, Wauconda, Port Barrington, Fox Lake, Ridgefield,
Winthrop Harbor, Round Lake Beach, Hainesville, Pistakee Highlands,
Huntley, Grayslake, Gurnee, Channel Lake, Round Lake Heights,
Lakewood, Russell, Wadsworth, Volo, Round Lake, Crystal Lake, Long
Lake, Third Lake, Lake Catherine, Grandwood Park, and Zion.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
